<section id="install"><title id="install.title">Installation</title>

    <section id="download"><title id="download.title">Download</title>

        <para>
        The CLI library can downloaded from
        <ulink url="http://alexis.royer.free.fr/CLI/index.html#download">here</ulink>
        in the form of gzipped archives.
        </para>

    </section>

    <section id="prerequisit"><title id="prerequisit.title">Prerequisit</title>

        <para>
        The CLI library needs nothing special when compiled on Linux.
        You will have however to install cygwin if you compile it on Windows.
        </para>

    </section>

    <section id="compilation"><title id="compilation.title">Compilation</title>

        <para>
        Once you have downloaded the archive, unpack it on your disk:
        <programlisting>tar xvfz cppcli-1.0.tgz</programlisting>
        </para>

        <para>
        Go to <filename class="directory">cpp/build/make</filename>:
            <programlisting>cd cpp/build/make</programlisting>
        And compile:
            <programlisting>make</programlisting>
        This compilation will run over the following steps:
            <orderedlist>
            <listitem>Compilation of the CLI library for C++</listitem>
            <listitem>Compilation of program samples: cpptest, empty, clisample</listitem>
            <listitem>User guide samples testing: all samples of this user guide are compiled, executed, and checked</listitem>
            <listitem>Additional unit tests: io_device</listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>

    </section>

</section>

